spans.text: ( if successive vanities can spare One thought to love ) what cruel pangs I bear , Left in these plains all wretched , and alone , To weep with fountains , and with echoes groan , And mourn incessantly that fatal day , That all my bliss with CHLOE snatched away
if successive vanities can spare One thought to
my soul , or sooth my cares
for aid from POPE'S and PRIOR'S Muse
panting EMMA sighs in HENRY'S arms
CAM'S old urn its silver current yields , Where solemn towers overlook each mossy grove , As if to guard it from the assaults of love
